  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 5 following Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification. Decision: Accepted. NOTE (adversarial): the ContextOfUse description enumerates operating ranges in narrative prose but no hasOperatingEnvelope or hasApplicabilityConstraint link is emitted, leaving the model's bounded domain of validity formally unspecified.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-cou2-accepted",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/hemolysis-experimental-mrl5"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "type": "ContextOfUse",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment. Operating conditions span blood temperatures of 36–38 °C, inlet pressures of 5–15 mmHg, outlet pressures of 60–120 mmHg, volumetric flow rates of 3–7 L/min, and impeller speeds of 2 000–3 500 RPM, covering laminar-to-transitional flow regimes (Reynolds numbers 800–4 200 based on impeller tip diameter). Fluid properties assume human whole blood at 37 °C with hematocrit 40 ± 5 %, dynamic viscosity 3.5 ± 0.5 mPa·s, and density 1 055 ± 10 kg/m³. These ranges reflect the intended clinical envelope for chronic VAD support in adult patients.",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "decisionConsequence": "High"
  },
